  "texts": [
    "Additional studies like Kobylinski and Pochwatko (2020) focused on movement detection in VR narration.",
    "Sterna et al. (2021) proposed an ideal design for psychophysiological and eye-tracking measurement in VR, emphasizing the fixations count.",
    "Mirault et al. (2020) analyzed transposed-word effects on reading using eyetracking metrics in VR such as fixations count, dwell-time and gaze position.",
    "Maraj et al. (2021) investigated immersion and comfort using eye-tracked VR devices, concluding no significant difference in user responses.",
    "Jurik et al. (2019) explored the use of eye-tracking in VR, advocating for its potential in cross-cultural studies on human perception and cognition."
